This paper discusses the representation and analysis of dependencies in graphical structures, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of directed acyclic graphs (DAGs) also suggests a potential connection to databases (cs.DB). The mention of functional and conditional dependencies may also relate to information theory (cs.IT) and social networks (cs.SI).
